#cleaning
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
clean_list = []
for text in df['Headline']:
    words = regexp_tokenize(text.lower(), r'[A-Za-z]+')
    words = [w for w in words if len(w)>1 and w not in stopwords.words('english')]
    words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(w) for w in words]
    clean_list.append(' '.join(words))

df['Clean_Headline'] = clean_list

4. TFIDF¶

The rationale behind using TFIDS is to weigh co-occuraning words with n-gram in each document

In [16]:
#creating TF-IDF vectorizer
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
tfidf_vect = TfidfVectorizer(analyzer='word', token_pattern=r'\w{1,}',ngram_range=(1,3),min_df=0.15,max_features=5000)
tfidf_matrix =  tfidf_vect.fit_transform(df1['Clean_Headline'])

K means clustering¶

In [17]:
# finding optimum "K" value
K = range(1, 8)
kmeans = [KMeans(n_clusters=i) for i in K]
score = [kmeans[i].fit(tfidf_matrix).score(tfidf_matrix) for i in range(len(kmeans))]
plt.plot(K, score)
plt.xlabel('Clusters')
plt.ylabel('Score')
plt.title('Optimal K Elbow Curve')
plt.show()

In [22]:
def plot_cluster_2D_TSNE(vectors,clusters):
    #dim reduction using TSNE to plot clusters in 2D 
    from sklearn.manifold import TSNE
    tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, init='random', random_state=42, perplexity=50)
    pos = tsne.fit_transform(vectors) 
    xs, ys = pos[:, 0], pos[:, 1]

    # Set up cluster names using a dict
    cluster_names = {0: 'Cluster 1', 1: 'Cluster 2', 2: 'Cluster 3', 3: 'Cluster 4'}
    cluster_colors = {0: '#990c36', 1: '#141edb', 2: '#ecf00e', 3: '#e7298a'}

    # Plot clusters
    df_plot = pd.DataFrame(dict(x=xs, y=ys, label=clusters)) 
    groups = df_plot.groupby('label')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 7))

    for name, group in groups:
        ax.plot(group.x, group.y, marker='o', linestyle='', ms=10, 
                label=cluster_names[name], color=cluster_colors[name], mec='none')
        ax.set_aspect('auto')
        ax.tick_params(axis= 'x',  which='both', bottom='off', top='off', labelbottom='off')
        ax.tick_params(axis= 'y', which='both', left='off', top='off', labelleft='off')
    ax.legend(numpoints=1) 
    plt.show()
    return

5. Word2Vec¶

In [39]:
token_list = [simple_preprocess(i) for i in df['Clean_Headline']]
corpus = np.array(token_list)

model = Word2Vec(corpus, size=100, min_count=2, sample=1e-3, sg=0, iter=5, workers=10)
vocab = set(model.wv.index2word)
In [44]:
features = 100
def Min_max_word_vectors(words, model, vocabulary, num_features):
    max_feature_vector = np.zeros((features,), dtype="float64")
    min_feature_vector = np.zeros((features,), dtype="float64")
    for word in words:
        if word in vocabulary: 
            max_feature_vector = np.maximum(max_feature_vector, model.wv[word])
            min_feature_vector = np.minimum(min_feature_vector, model.wv[word])
    feature_vector = np.concatenate((max_feature_vector,min_feature_vector))
    return feature_vector
features = [Min_max_word_vectors(sent_tokens, model, vocab, features) for sent_tokens in corpus]
min_max_features = np.array(features)

# Plot of distribution of topics in clusters with different methods
def distplot(X1,X2,Y):
    plt.figure(figsize=(30, 8))
    plt.subplot(131)
    sns.countplot(data=df1,x=X1,hue=Y)
    plt.title('KMeans')

    plt.subplot(132)
    sns.countplot(data=df1,x=X2,hue=Y)
    plt.title('Agglomerative')
    plt.suptitle('Distribution of topics : K-means Vs Agglormerative')
    plt.show()
print("________________________________________________TFIDF______________________________________________________")
distplot('cluster_kmeans_tfidf','cluster_agg_tfidf','Topic')

distplot('kmeans_wordvec','kmeans_wordvec','Topic')

Observations:¶

After trying 6 combinations of using TF-IDF,Word2vec & Doc2vec, I dont see any pattern in the results. All of them are quite different from each other

On this particular sample 10K sample, Doc2Vec K-Means/Agglomerative clustering didn't perform satisfactorily. Both approaches formed more clusters than the topics

Relative to the above approaches, I can say TF-IDF performed better, but couldn't cluster topics in 1-2 categories with K-means/agglomerative

Word2Vec kind of performed better compared to TF-IDF/Doc2Vec, and K-means better compared to Agglomerative in this sample.
